Amidst the vague exclamations of bigotry and hatred, the Turks arc not accnsed of a wanton or immoderate effuslon of Christian blood: but according to their maxims (the maxims of antiquity)‚ the lives of the vanquished were forfeited; and the legitimate reward of the conqueror was derived from the service, the sale„ or the ransom, of his captives of both sexes ⁶⁹.
